caption.text:
There are cheerios EVERYWHERE..😳

I hate to be the bearer of bad news, but saying a catchy one-liner to cam just doesn’t cut in anymore when it comes to hooks 🙄

Comment “playbook” & I’ll fire over a guide with everything you need to improve your hook-game! Inside I’ve included my 5 Elements of a Strong Hook framework AND 25+ hook templates you can use right now 🥳

ps. to make sure you get it, be sure to check your requests folder & be following.

Happy creating! ✨

caption.text:
I really hope somebody tries this… 👀 

ALSO: We’re working on a new project, and we’d love to get you all involved. 

Last week we sat down to talk about how we’d go viral in 2024. We discussed different formats, shared our favourite videos, and grilled each other a bit… and we filmed it all as a ‘Pilot’ episode for a podcast.

Anyone in sales, cooking, or coaching will probably find this especially entertaining/helpful. But there’s valuable takeaways for every type of creator! 

We’d love to know how we can improve and make this more valuable for you. Maybe we analyze your videos? Bring in special guests? Highlight success stories from students? 

Watch the video on YouTube and share your thoughts over there! (you know where to find the 🔗)

caption.text:
Earlier this year I set out on a mission.

A mission to get paid to pursue one of my life’s biggest passions.

But I never dreamed it could’ve turned into what it has today.

Our goal at One Peak is to “Empower people to do bring their ideas to life”

To make that goal possible; this is our core belief - ‘If you can learn to create content, you can get paid to do the things you’re deeply passionate about’.

I love this core belief because it enables people to ‘Live in their fire’.

That’s what my life coach @iamedwardmjb encouraged me to do when I told him about this ridiculous idea I had to try to get paid to play golf.

It felt irresponsible.

It felt like something you do when you’re retired.

It didn’t feel impactful.

But as Ed so graciously explained to me - “It’s better to live a life filled with passion than a half hearted attempt at righteousness.”

When you live in your fire, it impacts the way you show up each day. It allows you to bring a new level of energy to your relationships, and ultimately it makes the world a better place.

So maybe if I prove to myself that it’s possible - I can show others it is too?

Over 6 months I was able to grow an amazing fan base of 45,000 fellow golfers, and get an incredible title sponsorship from one of the fastest growing brands in golf. 

But to me that really wasn’t what mattered.

This project proved that if I could do it - anyone can. All they had to do was learn to create content that gets attention. 

This is a skill we’ve been perfecting at One Peak for the last 5 years. 

A skill we’ve consolidated into our “TikTok & Reels Creator Course”

And a skill that is starting to change the lives of students like @jordanoelrichgolf

For anyone who’s reading this and has been part of our journey over the years at One Peak - thank you.

Thank you so so much for giving us this platform, watching and supporting us as we grow, and allowing us to share what we’ve learned with the 
world. None of this could have happened without you 
❤️
.
.
